<p class="small">
<strong>Arsenal analytics</strong>: scraping FBref, building match and player trackers, and testing simple forecasting ideas on xG and roles. Eventually I want to combine this with my thesis and be able to out-predict gambling player props. Right now I'm in the data collection phase for my thesis. I need data from 25 teams and over 20 players per team. Twice now data scrapers I've built have been patched which has slowed the process.
<br><br>
<strong>Marketing analytics</strong>: building a structure for marketing analytics at North Pier. I want to increase our social media presence and in order to do that I need to know what works and what doesn't
<br><br>
<strong>Cash Balance project</strong>: classified work project cleaning 5500 outputs for cash balance plan returns and basic validation checks.
<br><br>
<strong>LEGO price prediction project</strong>: focusing on a sub-theme like Star Wars or Batman. I want to understand what drives the after-market value.
